    <stitle>TSI 08-08-01 - High Voltage and Hybrid Pre-Service Checklist</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi080801" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>08-08-01</tsinumber>
        <replace>
            <tsinumber>07-08-02</tsinumber>
        </replace>
        <tsidate>April, 2008</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Electrical</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>High Voltage and Hybrid Pre-Service Checklist</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <distribution dealer="yes" fleet="yes" bodybuilder="no" isis_cd="yes"/>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>High Voltage can be hazardous and may exist on trucks in a number of different systems and
                    components such as hybrid electric systems, auxiliary power units, and inverters to name just a few.
                </para>
                <para>Below is a "Pre-Service Checklist" to help ensure proper work practices when performing service on
                    vehicles equipped with high voltage or hybrid components.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Shock hazard. Only trained technicians should service high voltage components. High
                            voltage circuits and components contain voltage levels that may cause equipment damage,
                            electric shock, and/or deadly electrocution if handled incorrectly.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
                <table id="t0808011" tblwidth="pg-wide" frame="all">
                    <title>Checklist</title>
                    <tgroup cols="2">
                        <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.45*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.55*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>(&#8730;) CHECK</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>ACTION</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Review
                                        <exhotlnk document="../tsis/060805.htm" bookname="tsi">TSI 06-08-05.</exhotlnk>
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Set park brake.</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Chock wheels.</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Insure that bay and vehicle are adequately illuminated and clean.</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Verify that an
                                        <emph type="bold">ABC rated</emph>
                                        fire extinguisher is close by and charged.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para></para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Identify high voltage equipment on the vehicle.</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>&#160;</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Refer to manufacturer's service publications on identified high voltage
                                        components for service and high voltage isolation procedure(s).
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Identify a coworker who will remain nearby. It is recommended that at least
                                        one person at the location be trained in CPR.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Place orange cones (included in the
                                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE 5017</emph>
                                        Tool Kit) at the four corners of the vehicle (refer to Figures 1-3).
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Affix warning signs (included in the
                                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE 5017</emph>
                                        Tool Kit) on the vehicle (refer to Figures 1-3).
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Install steering wheel cover (included in the
                                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE 5017</emph>
                                        Tool Kit) on steering wheel (refer to Figure 4).
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Remove all jewelry.</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Put on the Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) included in the
                                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE 5017</emph>
                                        Tool Kit.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Perform (according to the manufacturer's service publications) any diagnostics
                                        or work that require the high voltage system(s) to be enabled.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Put keys in your pocket &#8722;
                                        <emph type="bold">DO NOT LEAVE IN IGNITION!</emph>
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Isolate High Voltage (according to the manufacturer's service publications).
                                        <emph type="bold">Use lockouts if provided.</emph>
                                        Install the service disconnect warning tag (included in the
                                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE 5017</emph>
                                        Tool Kit) at disconnect (refer to Figure 5).
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Install block-out plug(s) and warning tags (included in the
                                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE 5017</emph>
                                        Tool Kit) into all shore power, charge, and other plug-in locations as necessary
                                        (refer to Figure 6).
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Perform (according to the manufacturer's service publications) any work or
                                        diagnostics that may be performed with the high voltage system(s) disabled.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry></entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">OPTIONAL SUGGESTION</emph>
                                        - Use "Caution" tape (included in the
                                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE 5017</emph>
                                        Tool Kit) to create a working zone around the vehicle as needed (refer to
                                        Figures 1-3).
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Each truck and bus is different; the following figures are provided as examples. The
                            objective is to alert others that high voltage equipment is being serviced (to prevent
                            inadvertent activation of any disabled high voltage circuits) and to provide a working zone
                            around the vehicle.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
